Note: ========================================
Note: HIR to OpenAPI Generator
Note: ========================================
Note: Generates valid OpenAPI 3.x YAML from Runa HIR

Note: Part of the Translation translation system - OpenAPI backend

Note: Generation Strategy:
Note:   - Produces OpenAPI 3.x compliant YAML
Note:   - Proper YAML indentation (2 spaces per level)
Note:   - Complete API specification with all fields
Note:   - Semantic validation during generation
Note: ========================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/openapi/openapi_parser.runa" as Parser

Note: ========================================
Note: OpenAPI Value Cell kinds (must match openapi_parser.runa)
Note: ========================================
Note: Every HIR value is a 16-byte tagged cell {kind @0, payload @8}.
Note: The cell accessors live in openapi_parser.runa
Note: (Parser.cell_kind / Parser.cell_payload).

Constant OAVAL_SCALAR as Integer is 1
Constant OAVAL_DICT as Integer is 2
Constant OAVAL_LIST as Integer is 3

Note: ========================================
Note: Top-Level Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Public entry point for HIR-to-OpenAPI translation. Owns the emitter
lifecycle so the caller only deals with the input HIR dictionary and the
returned YAML string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Constructs a raw byte emitter, dispatches generate_document on the HIR
root, extracts the accumulated YAML through emitter_raw_get_output, and
destroys the emitter. The caller owns the returned buffer.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_openapi_from_hir" takes hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate OpenAPI YAML from HIR dictionary
    Note: Returns: Pointer to null-terminated YAML string

    Let emitter be proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon

    proc generate_document with emitter, hir

    Let output be proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter

    proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter

    Return output
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Document Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
The OpenAPI 3.x root document has a fixed set of optional and required
top-level keys (openapi, info, servers, paths, components, security,
tags, externalDocs). Emitting them in the canonical order keeps the
output predictable and human-readable.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Looks up each canonical key in the HIR dictionary; for each present key,
emits the key, colon, newline, then delegates the value to the
appropriate sub-emitter (generate_info, generate_servers, etc.) at
indent level 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_document" takes emitter as Integer, hir as Integer:
    Note: Generate complete OpenAPI document

    Note: hir is an OAVAL_DICT cell; extract its inner Dict (key -> value cell)
    Let hir_dict be proc cell_payload from Parser with hir
    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Generate openapi version (scalar cell)
    Let openapi_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "openapi"
    Let openapi_cell be proc get from Dict with hir_dict, openapi_key

    If openapi_cell is not equal to 0:
        Let openapi_version be proc cell_payload from Parser with openapi_cell
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "openapi"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ": "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, openapi_version
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    End If

    Note: Generate info object (required) - dict cell
    Let info_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "info"
    Let info_cell be proc get from Dict with hir_dict, info_key

    If info_cell is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "info"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_info with emitter, info_cell, 1
    End If

    Note: Generate servers array (optional) - list cell
    Let servers_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "servers"
    Let servers_cell be proc get from Dict with hir_dict, servers_key

    If servers_cell is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "servers"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_servers with emitter, servers_cell, 1
    End If

    Note: Generate paths object (required) - dict cell
    Let paths_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "paths"
    Let paths_cell be proc get from Dict with hir_dict, paths_key

    If paths_cell is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "paths"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_paths with emitter, paths_cell, 1
    End If

    Note: Generate components object (optional) - dict cell
    Let components_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "components"
    Let components_cell be proc get from Dict with hir_dict, components_key

    If components_cell is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "components"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_components with emitter, components_cell, 1
    End If

    Note: Generate security array (optional) - list cell
    Let security_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "security"
    Let security_cell be proc get from Dict with hir_dict, security_key

    If security_cell is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "security"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_security with emitter, security_cell, 1
    End If

    Note: Generate tags array (optional) - list cell
    Let tags_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "tags"
    Let tags_cell be proc get from Dict with hir_dict, tags_key

    If tags_cell is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "tags"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_tags with emitter, tags_cell, 1
    End If

    Note: Generate externalDocs object (optional) - cell (dict)
    Let external_docs_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "externalDocs"
    Let external_docs_cell be proc get from Dict with hir_dict, external_docs_key

    If external_docs_cell is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "externalDocs"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_generic_object with emitter, external_docs_cell, 1
    End If
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Info Object Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
The info block has a flat structure (title, version, description,
license, contact). Reusing generate_generic_object avoids hard-coding the
field list and lets new fields appear automatically.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to generate_generic_object with the supplied indent level.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_info" takes emitter as Integer, info_obj as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate info object (title, version, description, etc.)

    proc generate_generic_object with emitter, info_obj, indent_level
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Servers Array Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
The servers array uses a hand-rolled emitter (instead of the generic list
helper) because the OpenAPI canonical form puts "url" inline with the
dash and "description" on a continuation line; that layout is more
readable than the alternative.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the servers list. For each entry: emits indent + "- url: <url>"
+ newline, then if a description exists, emits one indent deeper +
"description: <desc>" + newline.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_servers" takes emitter as Integer, servers_cell as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate servers array (list cell of server dict cells)

    Let servers_array be proc cell_payload from Parser with servers_cell
    If servers_array is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let server_count be proc size from List with servers_array
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than server_count:
        proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "- url: "

        Let server_cell be proc get from List with servers_array, i
        Let server_obj be proc cell_payload from Parser with server_cell

        Note: Get and emit URL (scalar cell)
        Let url_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "url"
        Let url_cell be proc get from Dict with server_obj, url_key

        If url_cell is not equal to 0:
            Let url_value be proc cell_payload from Parser with url_cell
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, url_value
            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        End If

        Note: Get and emit description if present (scalar cell)
        Let desc_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "description"
        Let desc_cell be proc get from Dict with server_obj, desc_key

        If desc_cell is not equal to 0:
            Let desc_value be proc cell_payload from Parser with desc_cell
            proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level plus 1
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "description: "
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, desc_value
            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Paths Object Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
"paths" is a dictionary keyed by URL pattern; each value is a path-item
object whose keys are HTTP methods plus shared parameter declarations.
The two-level shape requires its own emitter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the paths dictionary keys; for each key, emits indent + the
path string + ":" + newline, then dispatches the path item through
generate_path_item at one deeper indent.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_paths" takes emitter as Integer, paths_cell as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate paths object with all endpoints (dict cell)

    Let paths_obj be proc cell_payload from Parser with paths_cell
    If paths_obj is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let path_keys be proc keys from Dict with paths_obj
    Let path_count be proc size from List with path_keys
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than path_count:
        Let path_key be proc get from List with path_keys, i
        Let path_item_cell be proc get from Dict with paths_obj, path_key

        Note: Emit path
        proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, path_key
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10

        Note: Generate path item (operations) -- dict cell
        proc generate_path_item with emitter, path_item_cell, indent_level plus 1

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
A path item mixes HTTP method operations with other keys (parameters,
summary, servers). The two are emitted differently: operations get
dispatched through generate_operation, anything else through the generic
value emitter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the path item dictionary keys; uses is_http_method to
discriminate. HTTP method keys emit "method:" + newline followed by
generate_operation; other keys emit "key:" + newline followed by
generate_value.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_path_item" takes emitter as Integer, path_item_cell as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate path item with HTTP operations (dict cell)

    Let path_item be proc cell_payload from Parser with path_item_cell
    If path_item is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let item_keys be proc keys from Dict with path_item
    Let key_count be proc size from List with item_keys
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than key_count:
        Let key be proc get from List with item_keys, i
        Let value be proc get from Dict with path_item, key

        Note: Check if this is an HTTP method
        Let is_method be proc is_http_method from Parser with key

        If is_method is equal to 1:
            Note: Generate operation (operation dict cell)
            proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, key
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10

            proc generate_operation with emitter, value, indent_level plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Note: Generate other fields (like shared parameters) as a value cell
            proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, key
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"

            proc generate_value with emitter, value, indent_level plus 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Operation Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Operation objects (summary, description, parameters, responses, etc.)
have free-form structure; routing them through the generic emitter avoids
hardcoding the schema.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to generate_generic_object at the supplied indent level.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_operation" takes emitter as Integer, operation as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate operation object (summary, parameters, responses, etc.)

    proc generate_generic_object with emitter, operation, indent_level
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Components Object Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Components groups reusable schemas, parameters, responses, requestBodies
etc.; its shape is regular enough to delegate to generate_generic_object.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to generate_generic_object at the supplied indent level.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_components" takes emitter as Integer, components as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate components object (schemas, responses, parameters, etc.)

    proc generate_generic_object with emitter, components, indent_level
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Security Array Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Security requirements are an array of objects; each entry needs its own
"- " marker followed by a generic value dispatch.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the security_array list; for each entry emits indent + "- "
then dispatches the requirement through generate_value at the next
indent level.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_security" takes emitter as Integer, security_cell as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate security requirements array (list cell)

    Let security_array be proc cell_payload from Parser with security_cell
    If security_array is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let security_count be proc size from List with security_array
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than security_count:
        Let security_req be proc get from List with security_array, i

        Let kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with security_req

        If kind is equal to OAVAL_DICT:
            Note: Security requirement object -- compact "- scheme: [...]" form
            proc generate_dict_as_list_item with emitter, security_req, indent_level
        Otherwise:
            proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "- "
            proc generate_value with emitter, security_req, indent_level plus 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Tags Array Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Tags are conventionally rendered with name on the dash line and
description on a continuation line; this two-line shape is more readable
than nesting the full object structure.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates tags_array; for each tag emits indent + "- name: <name>"
+ newline, then if a description exists, emits one indent deeper +
"description: <desc>" + newline.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_tags" takes emitter as Integer, tags_cell as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate tags array (list cell of tag dict cells)

    Let tags_array be proc cell_payload from Parser with tags_cell
    If tags_array is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let tag_count be proc size from List with tags_array
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than tag_count:
        Let tag_cell be proc get from List with tags_array, i
        Let tag_obj be proc cell_payload from Parser with tag_cell

        proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "- name: "

        Let name_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "name"
        Let name_cell be proc get from Dict with tag_obj, name_key

        If name_cell is not equal to 0:
            Let name_value be proc cell_payload from Parser with name_cell
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, name_value
            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        End If

        Note: Emit description if present (scalar cell)
        Let desc_key be proc create_string_literal from Parser with "description"
        Let desc_cell be proc get from Dict with tag_obj, desc_key

        If desc_cell is not equal to 0:
            Let desc_value be proc cell_payload from Parser with desc_cell
            proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level plus 1
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "description: "
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, desc_value
            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Generic Value Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Central dispatcher for arbitrary OpenAPI values. Dictionaries and lists
each get a leading newline so the nested block starts on a fresh line;
scalars stay on the current line followed by a trailing newline.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null becomes "null\n". The value is a tagged cell: OAVAL_DICT emits "\n"
then recurses through generate_generic_object at the same indent;
OAVAL_LIST emits "\n" then recurses through generate_list; OAVAL_SCALAR
emits the payload String inline + "\n".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_value" takes emitter as Integer, value as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate any value cell (scalar, dict, list)

    If value is equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "null"
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        Return
    End If

    Let kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with value

    If kind is equal to OAVAL_DICT:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_generic_object with emitter, value, indent_level
        Return
    End If

    If kind is equal to OAVAL_LIST:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        proc generate_list with emitter, value, indent_level
        Return
    End If

    Note: Scalar cell -- emit the payload string
    Let scalar_str be proc cell_payload from Parser with value
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, scalar_str
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
End Process

@Reasoning:
The generic object emitter handles the "anything goes" parts of OpenAPI -
info, components, schemas - by emitting key/value lines and recursing
for nested compound values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
The obj argument is an OAVAL_DICT cell; extract its inner Dict. Iterate
the dictionary keys; for each key emit indent + "key: ", then dispatch
the value cell: OAVAL_DICT gets "\n" + nested generate_generic_object,
OAVAL_LIST gets "\n" + generate_list, OAVAL_SCALAR gets inline emission.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_generic_object" takes emitter as Integer, obj as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate generic dictionary cell as YAML object

    Let obj_dict be proc cell_payload from Parser with obj
    If obj_dict is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let obj_keys be proc keys from Dict with obj_dict
    Let key_count be proc size from List with obj_keys
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than key_count:
        Let key be proc get from List with obj_keys, i
        Let value be proc get from Dict with obj_dict, key

        proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, key

        Let kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with value

        If kind is equal to OAVAL_DICT:
            Note: Compound value -- "key:" then nested block on following lines
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
            proc generate_generic_object with emitter, value, indent_level plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If kind is equal to OAVAL_LIST:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
                proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
                proc generate_list with emitter, value, indent_level plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Note: Scalar cell -- "key: value" inline
                Let value_str be proc cell_payload from Parser with value
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ": "
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, value_str
                proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Generic list emitter for any OpenAPI array. Each item gets a "- " marker
followed by the appropriate value emission shape based on the item cell
kind.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
The list argument is an OAVAL_LIST cell; extract its inner List. Iterate
the list; for each item-cell emit indent + "- ", then dispatch:
OAVAL_DICT gets "\n" + nested generate_generic_object, OAVAL_LIST gets
"\n" + nested generate_list, OAVAL_SCALAR gets inline emission.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_list" takes emitter as Integer, list as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate list cell as YAML array

    Let list_payload be proc cell_payload from Parser with list
    If list_payload is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let item_count be proc size from List with list_payload
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than item_count:
        Let item be proc get from List with list_payload, i

        Let kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with item

        If kind is equal to OAVAL_DICT:
            Note: Render a mapping item compactly: "- firstkey: ..." with the
            Note: remaining keys aligned one level deeper. The dash-then-newline
            Note: form is intentionally avoided because it is harder to re-parse.
            proc generate_dict_as_list_item with emitter, item, indent_level
        Otherwise:
            If kind is equal to OAVAL_LIST:
                proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "-"
                proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
                proc generate_list with emitter, item, indent_level plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Note: Scalar cell -- "- value"
                proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "- "
                Let item_str be proc cell_payload from Parser with item
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, item_str
                proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
A mapping that is a YAML block-sequence element must render with its first
key on the dash line ("- key: value") and every subsequent key aligned to
the column just past the dash (indent_level + 1). This compact form is the
round-trip-safe shape; emitting a bare dash followed by an indented block
mapping on the next line is valid YAML in principle but is not accepted by
the shared YAML block parser, so we never produce it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Extract the item's inner Dict. Emit indent + "- ". For the first key, emit
it inline (scalar -> "key: value\n"; compound -> "key:\n" + nested block at
indent_level + 2). For each remaining key, emit_indent(indent_level + 1)
then the same key/value shape. An empty mapping emits just "- \n".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_dict_as_list_item" takes emitter as Integer, item as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Render a dictionary cell as a compact YAML block-sequence element

    Let item_dict be proc cell_payload from Parser with item

    proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "- "

    If item_dict is equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        Return
    End If

    Let item_keys be proc keys from Dict with item_dict
    Let key_count be proc size from List with item_keys

    If key_count is equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
        Return
    End If

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than key_count:
        Let key be proc get from List with item_keys, i
        Let value be proc get from Dict with item_dict, key

        If i is greater than 0:
            Note: Continuation keys align past the dash (one level deeper)
            proc emit_indent with emitter, indent_level plus 1
        End If

        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, key

        Let kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with value

        If kind is equal to OAVAL_DICT:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
            proc generate_generic_object with emitter, value, indent_level plus 2
        Otherwise:
            If kind is equal to OAVAL_LIST:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ":"
                proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
                proc generate_list with emitter, value, indent_level plus 2
            Otherwise:
                Note: Scalar cell -- "key: value"
                Let value_str be proc cell_payload from Parser with value
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ": "
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, value_str
                proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Generic two-space indentation helper used by every list and object
emitter so nesting depth is consistent across the file.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Multiplies indent_level by 2 and emits that many ASCII space (32) bytes.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_indent" takes emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Emit indentation (2 spaces per level)

    Let spaces_needed be indent_level multiplied by 2
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than spaces_needed:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32  Note: space
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Convenience wrapper to emit a single line terminator. Centralising it
keeps callers free of the magic byte value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits a single LF (10) byte through the raw emitter.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_newline" takes emitter as Integer:
    Note: Emit newline character

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10  Note: \n
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Shared helpers
Note: ========================================
Note: The HTTP-method predicate (is_http_method) and the string-literal key
Note: wrapper (create_string_literal) live in openapi_parser.runa and are
Note: shared here via the Parser alias, so each is defined exactly once
Note: across the frontend and backend.
